{{refimprove|date=August 2012}} {{clear}} {{Infobox ecoregion | name = Alto Paraná Atlantic Forests | image = ArialViewIguazuFallsDistantNbr1of10.JPG | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = Aerial view of [[Iguaçu National Park]], [[Brazil]]. | country = {{BRA}} | country1 = {{ARG}} | country2 = {{PAR}} | state = [[São Paulo (state)]] | state1 = [[Mato Grosso do Sul]] | state2 = [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]] | state3 = [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]] | state4 = [[Minas Gerais]] | state5 = [[Goiás]] | state6 = [[Rio Grande do Sul]] | state7 = [[Misiones Province]] | border = [[Araucaria moist forests]] | border1 = [[Gran Chaco|Chaco]] | border2 = [[Cerrado]] | border3 = [[Serra do Mar coastal forests]] | bird_species = 586<ref name = "Atlas"/> | mammal_species = 213<ref name="Atlas"> {{cite book|last1=Hoekstra |first1=J. M. |last2=Molnar |first2=J. L. |last3=Jennings |first3=M. |last4=Revenga |first4=C. |last5=Spalding |first5=M. D. |last6=Boucher |first6=T. M. |last7=Robertson |first7=J. C. |last8=Heibel |first8=T. J. |last9=Ellison |first9=K. |title=The Atlas of Global Conservation: Changes, Challenges, and Opportunities to Make a Difference |publisher=[[University of California Press]] |editor1-last=Molnar |editor1-first=J. L. |year=2010 |isbn=978-0-520-26256-0 |url=http://www.nature.org/ourscience/sciencefeatures/conservation-atlas-1.xml |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404002733/http://www.nature.org/ourscience/sciencefeatures/conservation-atlas-1.xml |archivedate=2013-04-04 }}</ref> | habitat_loss = 94.0 | habitat_loss_ref = <ref name="wwf'">{{cite web|url=http://d3nehc6yl9qzo4.cloudfront.net/downloads/altoparana_versao_completa_portugues.pdf|title=Visão da Biodiversidade da Ecorregião das Florestas do Alto Paraná|year=2006}}</ref> | protected = 2.83 | protected_ref = <ref name = "Atlas"/> | area = 471204 | biome = [[Atlantic Forest]] | map = Alto Paraná Atlantic Forest.png | map_size = 240 | map_alt = | map_caption = }} The '''Alto Paraná Atlantic forests''', also known as the '''Paraná-Paraíba interior forests''', is an [[terrestrial ecoregion|ecoregion]] of the [[tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests|tropical moist forests]] [[Biome]], and the South American [[Atlantic Forest]] biome. It is located in southern [[Brazil]], northeastern [[Argentina]], and eastern [[Paraguay]].
==Geography== The Alto Paraná Atlantic forests are an interior extension of the coastal forests, extending across the southern portion of the [[Brazilian Highlands]]. The ecoregion extends from the mouth of the [[Paraíba do Sul River]] eastward along the Paraíba valley lying behind the coastal [[Serra do Mar]], and further eastward and northward along the basin of the [[Paraná River]] and its tributaries, forming a complex mosaic with the surrounding ecoregions.
[[File:Alto Paraná Atlantic forest.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Alto Paraná Atlantic forests ecoregion (within yellow line).]] [[File:Anodorhynchus glaucus.jpg|thumb|left|upright|[[Glaucous macaw]], an extinct endemic species formerly of this ecoregion.]] ;States, provinces, and departments The ecoregion covers portions of the Brazilian states of [[Rio de Janeiro State|Rio de Janeiro]], [[Minas Gerais]], [[São Paulo State|São Paulo]], [[Goiás]], [[Mato Grosso do Sul]], [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]], [[Santa Catarina State|Santa Catarina]], and [[Rio Grande do Sul]], the Argentinian province of [[Misiones Province|Misiones]], and the Paraguayan [[Departments of Paraguay|departments]] of Alto Paraná, Amambay, Caaguazu, Caazapa, Canindeyú, Concepción, Guairá, and Itapúa.
;Adjacent ecoregions The [[Cerrado]] lie to the north and east (in [[São Paulo (state)|São Paulo]]), entwining with the Paraná-Paraíba forests in a complex mosaic. The [[Serra do Mar coastal forests]] lie to the south, on the Atlantic side of the Serra do Mar range. The Alto Paraná Atlantic forests wrap around the north, east, and south of the [[Araucaria moist forests]], which cover a higher-elevation portion of the plateau in Paraná, Santa Catarina, and northern Rio Grande do Sul states. The [[Uruguayan savanna]] lies to the south, and to the west lie the [[Southern Cone Mesopotamian savanna]] and the [[Humid Chaco]] in Argentina and Paraguay, respectively.
==Climate== The climate of the ecoregion is subtropical, with {{Convert|1200|to|1600|mm|in}} of rainfall per year. The winter dry season extends from April to September.
==Flora== The main vegetation type is semi-deciduous forests, akin to the other interior forest ecoregions of the Atlantic forests. Approximately 40% of the trees lose their leaves during the winter dry season.
==See also== *[[List of plants of Atlantic Forest vegetation of Brazil]] *[[Atlantic Forest#Ecoregions|Ecoregions of the Atlantic Forest biome]]
