{{Infobox waterfall | name = Badaghagara Waterfall | native_name = ବଡ଼ଘାଗରା ଜଳପ୍ରପାତ | photo = Badaghagara_Kendujhar.jpg | photo_caption = Badaghagara Waterfall, Kendujhar | location = [[Kendujhar district]], [[Odisha]], [[India]] | coords = 21.6089, 85.5557 | elevation = | type = | height = {{convert|60|m}} | height_longest = | average_width = | number_drops = 1 | average_flow = | watercourse = Machha Kandana }}
The '''Badaghagara Waterfall''' is a waterfall of the [[Kendujhar district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Odisha]].
==Location== Badaghagara is located at a distance of 9&nbsp;km from the district headquarters ([[Kendujhar]]) of [[Kendujhar district]]. Being a perennial source of water, a dam has constructed on the downstream side. It is situated at a distance of 3 kilometers on the downstream of [[Sanaghagara Waterfall]].
==The falls== It is a perennial [[waterfall]]. The Machha Kandana, a small river, plunges from a height of {{convert|60|m}} in a single drop.
==See also== *[[List of waterfalls in India]] *[[List of waterfalls in India by height]]
