'''Khachindorbatly''' ({{lang-az|Xaçındərbətli}}, {{lang-hy|Արմենակավան / '''Armenakavan'''}}) is a village in the [[Agdam Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]]. Since the [[Nagorno-Karabakh war]] the town has been administered by the ''de facto'' [[Republic of Artsakh]] as part of [[Askeran Region|Askeran Province]].<ref>http://census.stat-nkr.am/nkr/1-1.pdf</ref>

