{{List of airports}}
[[Category:Lists of airports by ICAO code|V]] [[Category:Sri Lanka transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in Sri Lanka|Air]] [[Category:Cambodia transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Bangladesh transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Hong Kong transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Laos transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Macau-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Nepal transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Bhutan transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Maldives transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Thailand transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Vietnam transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Myanmar transport-related lists|Airports by ICAO code]] [[Category:Lists of airports in India| V]] [[Category:Chinese aviation-related lists| V]]

This is a list of countries and territories with a flag that incorporates the [[Union Jack]]. Six [[Commonwealth nation]]s have the Union Jack on their national flag. The first Commonwealth country to drop the Union Jack was [[Canada]] in 1965, after [[Flag of Canada|adopting a new national flag]]. The most recent country to drop the Union Jack from its flag was [[South Africa]] in 1994, after [[Flag of South Africa|adopting a new national flag]]. The only overseas territory without the Union Jack on its current flag is [[Gibraltar]].
The list also includes [[British Overseas Territories|overseas territories]], [[Province|provinces]] and [[Federated state|states]].
