A '''nephanalaysis''' is the analysis of a [[Synoptic scale meteorology|synoptic]] chart focusing on the types and amount of [[cloud]]s and [[precipitation]].<ref>Glossary of Meteorology. [http://amsglossary.allenpress.com/glossary/search?id=nephanalysis1 Nephanalysis.] Retrieved on 2008-01-22.</ref>  A nephanalysis can be used to avoid hazardous weather areas, by [[ship]]s preparing routes for cruises, and to locate good [[fishing]] areas.<ref>[[National Weather Service]]. [http://products.weather.gov/PDD/Neph.pdf?PHPSESSID=0313fbe9e5ff7e1f50b1aec867b0b8a8 Nephanalysis.] Retrieved on 2008-01-22.</ref>  This technique is rarely performed in modern forecasting, due to the prevalence of worldwide satellite imagery.<ref>AEROGRAPHER'S MATE 1&C. [http://www.tpub.com/content/aerographer/14010/css/14010_63.htm SHORT-RANGE EXTRAPOLATION.] Retrieved on 2008-01-22.</ref>

