{{italic title}}'''''Roots and Shadows''''' is an Indian novel, written by [[Shashi Deshpande]] in 1983.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Krushna_Mishra/publication/256533707_ROOTS_AND_SHADOWS_SHASHI_DESHPANDE%27S_MORAL_VISION_OF_A_WORLD_OF_REFORMED_RELATIONSHIPS/links/55bfe1ee08aec0e5f4476b52/ROOTS-AND-SHADOWS-SHASHI-DESHPANDES-MORAL-VISION-OF-A-WORLD-OF-REFORMED-RELATIONSHIPS.pdf?origin=publication_detail|title=Roots and Shadows: Shashi Deshpande's Moral Prescription for a Reformed World of Relationships as the Basis of the Indian TraditionaI Dream of Vasudpiva Kutumbakam|last=Mishro|first=Krushna Chandra|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> The novel focuses on Indu's interactions with others in her large family and the manner in which this helps to resolve their future and her own personal crisis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Award-winning-author-Shashi-Deshpande-resigns-in-protest/articleshow/49286139.cms|title=Deshpande's Rebellion|last=Fernandes|first=Joeanna Rebello|date=9 October 2015|website=The Times of India|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref>
