== Themes == * Marriage * Joint-family system * Infidelity * Class and caste relations * Feminism * Modernism
== Analysis and criticism == The work has been widely analysed and criticized for its feminist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inflibnet.ac.in/ojs/index.php/JLCMS/article/download/32/30|title=Feminism in Shashi Deshpande's Roots and Shadows|last=Prasad|first=N K|date=2010|website=Inflibnet|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> orientation. It has been a source for many thesis and papers on the role of women in society of today.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anubooks.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Notions-2014-No2-4.pdf|title=Identity motif's in Shashi Deshpande's Roots and Shadows|last=Ashok|first=K. Kumar|date=2014|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> The work is widely appreciated for bringing out the decaying joint family system in Indian society.
