[[File:Map of Shanghai in 上海县志.jpg|thumb|Map of the [[Old City of Shanghai]] in the Shanghai Xianzhi (上海县志).]] The '''Shanghai Xianzhi''' or "Shanghai Gazetteer" ({{zh|s=上海县志|p=Shànghǎi Xiànzhì}}) is an ancient [[gazetteer]] for the city of [[Shanghai]].<ref name="Brook">{{Cite book | title = The Confusions of Pleasure: Commerce and Culture in Ming China | first1 = Timothy | last1 = Brook | isbn = 978-0520-2215-43 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=YuMcHWWbXqMC | page = 310}}</ref> It is one of the numerous ''xianzhi'' ({{lang|zh-hans|县志}}, "county gazetteers") that were produced in China in ancient times.
An edition of the Shanghai Xianzhi is known from 1524.<ref name="Brook"/>
Another such document at the municipal rather than city level is the ''Shanghai Zhi'' ({{lang|zh-hans|上海志}}).<ref name="Brook"/>
